# ShopCursor Workshop - Cursor Rules
#
# NOTE: This file is supported but DEPRECATED in Cursor 2.0+.
# Prefer Project Rules in .cursor/rules/*.mdc for more control.
# See .cursor/rules/ for the migrated rules with auto-attachment by file type.

## Project Context
This is a 2-day Cursor IDE training workshop with a sample e-commerce app called "ShopCursor".
The app has a Java Spring Boot backend and a React TypeScript frontend.

## Tech Stack
- Backend: Java 17, Spring Boot 3.2, H2 in-memory database, JPA/Hibernate
- Frontend: React 18, TypeScript, Vite, plain CSS
- Testing: JUnit 5 (backend), Playwright (E2E)

## Coding Standards

### Java (Backend)
- Use Java 17 features (records, text blocks, pattern matching)
- Follow Spring Boot conventions for REST controllers
- Use constructor injection (not @Autowired on fields)
- Return ResponseEntity from controllers
- Keep services thin - business logic only

### TypeScript (Frontend)
- Use functional components with hooks
- Prefer interfaces over types for object shapes
- Use async/await over .then() chains
- Keep components under 150 lines
- Co-locate component CSS files

### General
- Use descriptive variable names
- Write meaningful commit messages
- Keep functions focused on a single responsibility
- Prefer early returns to reduce nesting

## Workshop Notes
- Some files contain INTENTIONAL code smells for refactoring exercises
- Files marked with "// WORKSHOP: Code smell" comments are meant to be improved
- Labs have starter/ and solution/ directories - don't peek at solutions early!
